'''Matthieu Epolo Luka''' (born 15 January 2005) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Standard Liège]]. Born in Belgium, he plays for the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

Epolo first became known to international football audiences for keeping six clean sheets in his first eight games of the [[2024–25 Belgian Pro League]] season, making him the most successful goalkeeper for shutouts in the top-20 ranked European leagues.<ref name="Epolocleansheets">{{cite news|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20240921_93339434|title=Geen doelman in Europa hield dit seizoen vaker de nul dan Standard-sluitstuk Matthieu Epolo: "Hij verdient dit na alle kritiek" (No goalkeeper in Europe has kept more clean sheets this season than Standard goalkeeper Matthieu Epolo: "He deserves this after all the criticism")|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|date=21 September 2024|access-date=25 September 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

== Club career ==
Epolo began playing football at KVK Wemmel and later [[FC Brussels]].<ref name=woos>{{cite news |last1=Woos |first1=Loïc |title=Une première dans un contexte particulier pour Matthieu Epolo : "On espérait plus de soutien de la part des supporters"|trans-title=A debut in a particular context for Matthieu Epolo: "We were hoping for more support from the fans"|url=https://www.walfoot.be/news/2024-04-30/une-premiere-dans-un-contexte-particulier-pour-matthieu-epolo--on-esperait-plus-de-soutien-de-la-part-des-supporters |access-date=3 October 2024 |publisher=WalFoot |date=30 April 2024 |language=French}}</ref> Epolo came through the youth academy of [[RSC Anderlecht]], moving to [[Standard Liège]] at the age of 14 in June 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Une promesse mauve file au Standard|trans-title=A purple promise joins Standard |url=https://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/2019/06/04/une-promesse-mauve-file-au-standard-22ZTAAWL2JCZJG7E2BC5Z7CSSY/ |access-date=3 October 2024 |work=[[La Dernière Heure]] |date=4 June 2019 |language=French}}</ref>

He made his professional debut on 26 August 2022 in the shirt of SL16 FC, the newly-launched Standard reserve team playing in the second-flight Challenger Pro League for the 2022–23 season. He started SL16's third match of the season against [[FCV Dender EH]], and ultimately shared game-time with SL16's other main goalkeeper Tom Poitoux, who played 19 games to Epolo's 18.

On 25 January 2023, shortly after his 18th birthday and with him being the third goalkeeper for the first team, Epolo extended his contract.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fiammetti |first1=Alexandre |title=Officiel : Le Standard de Liège prolonge Matthieu Epolo|trans-title=Official: Standard Liège extend Matthieu Epolo |url=https://www.walfoot.be/news/2023-01-25/officiel--le-standard-de-liege-prolonge-matthieu-epolo |access-date=3 October 2024 |publisher=WalFoot |date=25 January 2023 |language=French}}</ref>

Epolo was promoted to the first-team for the [[2023–24 Belgian Pro League]] season, and played the final five games of Standard's campaign, due to both transfer speculation and an injury for first-choice goalkeeper [[Arnaud Bodart]]. He made his league debut on 27 April 2024 against [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nl.soccerway.com/matches/2024/04/27/belgium/pro-league/standard-de-liege/sint-truidense-vv/4338768/|title= Standard vs. Sint-Truidense V.V. - 27 April 2024 - Soccerway|website=soccerway.com}}</ref> promoted by manager [[Ivan Leko]], amid reports that regular goalkeeper Bodart would leave at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Du changement et une grosse surprise dans le onze du Standard face à Saint-Trond|trans-title=Change and a big surprise in Standard's starting XI against Sint-Truiden|url=https://www.footnews.be/news/417115/du-changement-et-une-grosse-surprise-dans-le-onze-du-standard-face-a-sainttrond |access-date=3 October 2024 |work=Foot News |date=27 April 2024 |language=French}}</ref>

He enjoyed a 1–1 draw at home to [[Sint-Truidense V.V.|Sint-Truiden]] on his debut, with 20-year-old Mattéo Godfroid on the bench as Bodart was injured, according to Leko.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Woos |first1=Loïc |title=Qui sera le gardien du Standard pour terminer la saison ? Ivan Leko n'a pas laissé de place au doute !|trans-title=Who will be Standard's goalkeeper to end the season? |url=https://www.walfoot.be/news/2024-04-28/qui-sera-le-gardien-du-standard-pour-terminer-la-saison--ivan-leko-na-pas-laisse-de-place-au-doute |access-date=3 October 2024 |publisher=WalFoot |date=28 April 2024 |language=French}}</ref> Fewer than 10,000 fans saw his debut at the [[Stade Maurice Dufrasne]] due to a boycott of American owners [[777 Partners]], a situation Epolo said was understandable.<ref name=woos/> Leko said that Epolo would start the remaining games of the season.<ref name=woos/>

Further transfer speculation saw Bodart kept out of the first-team at the start of the following [[2024–25 Belgian Pro League|2024–25 season]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20240912_96947614|title=Leko heeft eindelijk zijn spits(en), maar krijgen we ook een offensiever Standard? "Nu begint het echte werk" (Leko finally has his striker(s), but will we also get a more offensive Standard? "Now the real work begins")|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|date=13 September 2024|access-date=25 September 2024|language=nl}}</ref> with Epolo starting as regular first-choice goalkeeper as a 19-year-old. Epolo kept clean sheets in Standard's first three games of the season against [[Racing Genk]], [[Club Brugge]] and [[KV Mechelen]] to give them an unbeaten start.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20240728_94899882|title=Blok op de doellijn en paal houden Karetsas en Genk van zege in bleke openingsmatch tegen Standard (Block on the goal line and post keep Karetsas and Genk from victory in pale opening match against Standard)|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|date=28 July 2024|access-date=25 September 2024|language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/394819|title=Club Brugge verslikt zich nu ook in Standard (1-0) en heeft competitiestart vollédig gemist (Club Brugge now also chokes against Standard (1-0) and has completely missed the start of the competition)|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|date=4 August 2024|access-date=25 September 2024|language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/live/voetbal/394821|title=Standard grijpt naast leidersplaats, maar blijft wel ongeslagen na scoreloos gelijkspel tegen KV Mechelen (Standard misses out on top spot, but remains unbeaten after scoreless draw against KV Mechelen)|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad|date=9 August 2024|access-date=25 September 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

Epolo went on to keep six clean sheets in his first eight league games of the season<ref>{{cite news |title=Nouvelle clean sheet pour Matthieu Epolo...qui s'est fait une belle frayeur : "J'ai eu de la chance sur ce coup-là"|trans-title=New clean sheet for Matthieu Epolo...who had a big scare: "I was lucky that time" |url=https://www.walfoot.be/news/2024-09-21/nouvelle-clean-sheet-pour-matthieu-epoloqui-sest-fait-une-belle-frayeur--jai-eu-de-la-chance-sur-ce-coup-la |access-date=16 October 2024 |work=Walfoot |author=Antoine Bourlon |date=21 September 2024 |language=French}}</ref> with Standard conceding only three goals in that time, scoring four to climb to the top half of the table. This run of clean sheets early in the season put Epolo top of the Belgian Pro League's official clean sheet table, with the best clean sheets record in Europe's top-20 ranked leagues, inspiring Standard to the best defensive record in the Pro League.<ref name="Epolocleansheets" /><ref>{{cite news |title=Matthieu Epolo: Standard Liege's teenage sensation in goal |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/matthieu-epolo-standard-lieges-teenage-sensation-in-goal-39966889 |access-date=16 October 2024 |work=OneFootball.com |date=30 August 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Sauvage |first1=Kevin |title=Trois buts encaissés, six clean-sheets et une place de choix dans le classement des portiers européens : les bons débuts de Matthieu Epolo au Standard|trans-title=Three goals conceded, six clean sheets and a choice place in the ranking of European goalkeepers: Mattheu Epolo's good start at Standard |url=https://www.lesoir.be/624383/article/2024-09-22/trois-buts-encaisses-six-clean-sheets-et-une-place-de-choix-dans-le-classement |access-date=3 October 2024 |work=[[Le Soir]] |date=22 September 2024 |language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Bleus |first1=Frédéric |title=Préparation intensive, réserves, déclic pendant l'hiver : comment le Standard a façonné Matthieu Epolo, le gardien qui a le plus de clean sheets|trans-title=Intensive preparation, reserves, spur during winter: how Standard built Matthieu Epolo, the goalkeeper who has the most clean sheets |url=https://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/standard/2024/09/24/preparation-intensive-reserves-declic-pendant-lhiver-comment-le-standard-a-faconne-matthieu-epolo-le-gardien-qui-a-le-plus-de-clean-sheets-4K4H3HEQ3NEC7NI3ZWXHGHC6QE/ |access-date=3 October 2024 |work=[[La Dernière Heure]] |date=24 September 2024 |language=French}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Belgium, Epolo is of DR Congolese descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/matthieu-epolo-standard-liege-teenage-095600863.html|title=Matthieu Epolo: Standard Liege's teenage sensation in goal|first1=Get|last1=Belgian|first2=Dutch Football News·2 min|last2=read|date=August 30, 2024|website=Yahoo Sports}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Belgium national under-17 football team|Belgium under-17 team]] for the [[2022 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]] in Israel. He played all three games in a group-stage elimination.<ref>{{cite news |title=Buitenspel gezet door corona, maar bomvol talent: alles wat u moet weten over EK van jongste Duivels|trans-title=Sidelined by corona, but full of talent: everything you need to know about the European Championship of the youngest Devils|url=https://sporza.be/nl/2022/05/16/buitenspel-gezet-door-corona-maar-bomvol-talent-alles-wat-u-moet-weten-over-ek-van-jongste-duivels~1652723416837/ |access-date=3 October 2024 |work=[[Sporza]] |date=17 May 2022 |language=Dutch}}</ref>

On 1 November 2025, Epolo received his maiden call-up to the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]] for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF second round|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifying play-offs]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Leopards name their squad for World Cup playoffs |url=https://www.cafonline.com/fifa-world-cup/news/leopards-name-their-squad-for-world-cup-playoffs |website=cafonline.com |access-date=16 November 2025 |language=en |date=1 November 2025}}</ref> On 12 November, his request to switch international allegiance to the DR Congo was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref name="FIFA-CAP"/> He debuted with the DR Congo in a 2–0 friendly win over [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]] on 16 December 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cvgr1k1l0y9t|title=Zambia vs Congo DR: Friendlies stats & head-to-head|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

